added.title: Brain Percentages
added.description: Beast Boy starts using more than 10% of his brain in an effort to find the hidden images in a puzzle.

added.title: Beast Man
added.description: Beast Boy discovers he can transform into an adult man.

added.title: Uncle Jokes
added.description: BB and Cyborg invite Starfire to join in their fun as long as she avoids dreaded uncle jokes.

added.title: The Bros
added.description: Darwin gets jealous of Gumball and Penny's relationship. When Darwin and Gumball reveal how they'd spend their perfect day, Gumball confesses that he would spend it with Penny. Darwin gets jealous and sets out to dig some dirt on Penny, hoping it will split them up. Meanwhile Gumball is planning to step his and Penny's relationship up a notch . . . by proposing marriage!

added.title: Sad Face
added.description: Once a month, while Jake's asleep, his tail stretches out of the treehouse to go work as a clown in a traveling bug circus.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Little Brother
added.description: Shelby is thrust into a new role after a party-related accident.

added.title: Lemonhope Part 1/Lemonhope Part 2
added.description: Lemonhope Part 1: Tired of all of Princess Bubblegum's talk about "responsibility," Lemonhope yearns for true freedom. So he sets off on the greatest adventure of his lemony life. Lemonhope Part 2: Though Lemonhope finds refuge from the desert with monster hunter Phlannel Boxingday, he might not be able to escape the ghosts of his past.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: Bad Timing
added.description: Love is in the air when Lumpy Space Princess reconnects with an old classmate, but will her jealousy get in the way of finding true love?

added.title: Ace Balthazar Lives
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to reunite the lead guitarist of Adrenaline with his band.

added.title: A Gift for Gus
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's present for Mr. Gus gets loose and causes trouble.

added.title: Picking Up Margaret
added.description: Mordecai wants to give Margaret a ride to the airport.

added.title: Cool Cubed
added.description: The guys need to unfreeze Thomas' brain after he chugs a slushy.

added.title: Trailer Trashed
added.description: Muscle Man's trailer fails a health inspection and he wants to keep it at all costs.

added.title: Meteor Moves
added.description: Mordecai wants to finally kiss Margaret at a meteor shower.

added.title: Rey del Castillo
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max viajan al Castillo Bishopbrook para visitar a un pariente lejano de la realeza. Pero cuando Ben se encuentra con un "fantasma" en la casa embrujada, resulta ser su nuevo rival, Kevin 11, que lanza a alienígenas aún más retorcidos en su camino: iThornblade, Undertow y Materia Oscura!

added.title: La Neblina del Paramo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson se hace internacional en el Omni-Copter, y la primera parada incluye una caminata por las Tierras Altas de Escocia. Pero el clima no es sólo malo, sino que hay niebla, y eso puede significa solamente una cosa: iel regreso de Niebla!

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Gwen 10
added.description: Gwen gets her hands on the Omnitrix and all its powers and now Ben has to take a backseat as Gwen 10 battles Vilgax for control of the device.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Sneaky Peeky
added.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

added.title: Hangry Hangry Hoppus
added.description: The Warriors battle a monster version of Hoppus, the rabbit transformed by the Cursed Garlic Magisword.

added.title: Jorts
added.description: When Mr. Gus gets stuck in an embarrassingly super tight pair of jorts, he has to somehow get out of them in order to save his friends.

added.title: Biggest Fan
added.description: An obsessed super fan goes to dangerous extremes just to be saved by her Warrior heroes: Vambre and Prohyas.

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: Insomnio en el Sena
added.description: Durante su estadía en París, Francia, Ben descubre a Zombozo en pleno robo en el Louvre. Pero cuando Zombozo hipnotiza a Ben para que se quede sin palabras, Ben debe navegar por una tierra extranjera como un mimo para detener al payaso criminal y su circo ambulante.

removed.title: Land of the Lost Shadows
removed.description: When pieces of their shadows are stolen by a shadow demon, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must travel to the Land of Lost Shadows in order to retrieve them.

removed.title: Astral Plane
removed.description: Finn has an out-of-body experience that takes him all over Ooo and beyond.

removed.title: Road Trippin'
removed.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

removed.title: Death Bear
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to get a picture in death bear's cage to impress Margaret and Eileen.

removed.title: Treasure Map
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

removed.title: Sugar Rush
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

removed.title: Last Laugh
removed.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

removed.title: Lil' Mac
removed.description: Mr. Gus' nephew terrorizes Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve.

removed.title: Be Sweet
removed.description: A fed up Lumpy Space Princess leaves the woods for a glamorous career in babysitting.

removed.title: The Pajama War
removed.description: A Candy Kingdom slumber party devolves into panic when Finn and Princess Bubblegum vanish.

removed.title: The Best VHS in the World
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

removed.title: Arrested Development
removed.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

removed.title: Many Happy Returns
removed.description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

removed.title: Malefactor
removed.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

removed.title: Out of Commission
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have one last day with the cart before they have to get rid of it.

removed.title: Big Tick
removed.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

removed.title: Kevin 11
removed.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

removed.title: Older
removed.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

removed.title: Gotta Get Grup to Get Down
removed.description: Grup hires the Warriors to help him become the biggest music star in Rhyboflaven, yet helping the little dragon achieve his big dream is no small task.

removed.title: On the Lam
removed.description: Finn's dad Martin the Human fights for freedom on a strange new planet!

removed.title: Showdown Part I
removed.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

removed.title: Cheep Thrills
removed.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

removed.title: Odd Bubbles Out
removed.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

removed.title: Outbreak
removed.description: When Dr. Psychobos steals a part out of the Omnitrix, causing chaotic side effects, it's up to Ben, Rook, and a small team of Plumbers get everything back to normal. (Introducing new Ben alien Kickin' Hawk, temp Ben alien Walkatrout, Upchuck Rook.)

removed.title: The Longest Weekend
removed.description: Muscle Man has to make it through a week without contacting Starla.

removed.title: High Dive
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa helps Samir overcome his paralyzing fear of the high dive.

removed.title: Gold Stars
removed.description: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig's child, Sweet P, runs into trouble on his first day of school.
